sql:
SELECT contributor_name
FROM contributors
WHERE contributions > 20;

SELECT repo_name
FROM repositories
WHERE owner = 'example_user2';

SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM repositories) AS total_repositories,
  (SELECT AVG(contributions) FROM contributors) AS avg_contributions;

external_knowledge:
- Significant contributions here denote the total number of commits made by a contributor. ;
- The term "top contributors" refers to the contributors with the highest number of commits, specifically the top 10 contributors. ;
- "GitHub handles" are synonymous with "GitHub usernames". ;

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT repo_id) AS unique_repos_count
FROM repositories
WHERE creation_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31' AND language = 'Python';

external_knowledge:
- 'A lot of activity' in this context means repositories with more than 10 issues;
- 'Top contributors' refers to those who have created a substantial number of issues, compared to other contributors in the same repository;
- The term 'very engaged' suggests a focus on contributors who have created a significant portion of the issues in each repository.

- "garden" metaphorically refers to the repository;
- "bloomed" metaphorically means repositories that were created;
- "diverse talents" metaphorically refers to distinct contributors;
- "floral community" metaphorically represents the collection of contributors in the repository.
